{
  "texts": [
    "In order to validate the effectiveness of the proposed method, we compare the proposed MMS-LLaMA with the previous state-of-the-art AVSR methods on LRS3 dataset, as shown in Table 1.",
    "Traditional approaches, such as CM-seq2seq (Ma et al., 2021), ViT3D-CM (Serdyuk et al., 2022), and auto-avsr (Ma et al., 2023), commonly employ Conformer-or Transformerbased backbones and rely on large-scale datasets to improve AVSR performances.",
    "Notably, LP Conformer (Chang et al., 2024) achieved a 0.9% WER using 100K hours of training data.",
    "More recent models, including Whisper-Flamingo (Rouditchenko et al., 2024) and LLaMA-AVSR (Cappellazzo et al., 2024), leverage large-scale pretrained models (e.g., Whisper and LLMs) and have demonstrated superior performance with WERs of 0.77% and 0.76%, respectively.",
    "Our MMS-LLaMA surpasses previous state-of-the-art methods, achieving a WER of 0.72% when trained on 1,759 hours of data."
  ]
}